
=============================
     Git Commands Cheat Sheet
     For Dev1 and Dev2 Branches
     Working on demo.txt
=============================

🔹 Common Setup (Both Dev1 & Dev2 - First Time Only)
---------------------------------------------------
git clone https://github.com/bhavneetv/ecoCycle.git
    cd ecoCycle

=============================
👨‍💻 DEV1 COMMANDS (Bhavneet)
=============================

✅ Create and Switch to Branch 'dev1'
git checkout -b dev1

✅ Make changes to demo.txt, then save and push
git add demo.txt
git commit -m "Dev1: updated demo.txt"
git push origin dev1

✅ Pull latest updates from dev1 branch
git checkout dev1
git pull origin dev1


=============================
📦 Push All Files in Project
=============================
git add .
git commit -m "Your commit message here"
git push origin dev1 


=============================
👨‍💻 DEV2 COMMANDS (VIpul)
=============================

✅ Create and Switch to Branch 'dev2'
git checkout -b dev2

✅ Make changes to demo.txt, then save and push
git add demo.txt
git commit -m "Dev2: updated demo.txt"
git push origin dev2

✅ Pull latest updates from dev2 branch
git checkout dev2
git pull origin dev2

=============================
📦 Push All Files in Project
=============================
git add .
git commit -m "Your commit message here"
git push origin dev2


=============================
🔁 After Merge on GitHub (All Devs)
=============================
git checkout main
git pull origin main


=============================
💡 One-Liner Commit + Push
=============================
git add demo.txt && git commit -m "Updated file" && git push origin dev1   # or dev2


=============================
📦 Push All Files in Project
=============================
git add .
git commit -m "Your commit message here"
git push origin dev1   # or dev2

# This adds and pushes ALL files and changes in the repo.
